{"questionId":"20356","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A particle moves in a straight line. The velocity,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>ms</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>,&nbsp;of the particle at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds is&nbsp;given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>t</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>10</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The following diagram shows the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/1a9e54ea1fc1e6317183726636b07d7b823a0dd4.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the acceleration of the particle when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognizing acceleration at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mn>7</mn></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>acceleration <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93430</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><msup><mtext>ms</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20356","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ1.5c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the acceleration of the particle when t=7.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.9—Kinematics problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}